# shellcheck configuration for loom (loom-n6uv)
#
# The gated lint runs at --severity=warning (see
# .claude/project-constitution.md canonical_commands.lint): style/info
# NOTES do not gate; real WARNINGS and above do. This file disables the
# one INFO-level code that is pervasive AND expected-by-design, so a
# plain `shellcheck` run (and editor integrations that default to the
# info floor) is also clean of known-benign noise — without masking any
# warning-or-above finding.
#
# Keep this list MINIMAL. Do NOT blanket-disable. Each entry below is a
# code that is (a) expected by loom's architecture and (b) pervasive
# (dozens of hits across the tree), so suppressing it repo-wide is
# correct rather than a band-aid. Per-site genuine findings get a real
# fix or an inline `# shellcheck disable=` with a justifying comment,
# never a repo-wide disable here.

# SC1091 — "Not following: ../lib/<file> was not specified as input."
# loom's hooks and scripts source their shared helpers dynamically via
# repo-relative paths resolved at runtime (e.g.
# `. "$(dirname "$0")/../lib/loom-hook-helpers.sh"`). shellcheck cannot
# follow these statically without `-x` plus a source-path, and the
# sourced files genuinely exist — the "not followed" note is a
# static-analysis limitation, not a defect. 65 occurrences across the
# tree. Expected and pervasive → disabled repo-wide.
disable=SC1091
